Chatto Mixed License Notice

Chatto uses per-file SPDX license metadata following the REUSE specification.
The canonical license metadata is in REUSE.toml and in any SPDX headers or
adjacent .license files present in the source tree.

The default repository license is the GNU Affero General Public License
version 3 or any later version (AGPL-3.0-or-later). This covers the Chatto
server, CLI, and bundled server release artifacts unless a more specific
license is declared.

Selected frontend, integration, and documentation surfaces are licensed under
the Apache License 2.0 (Apache-2.0), including the standalone frontend source
and image, public protocol/API definitions, generated TypeScript API
client/types, documentation, and examples as annotated in REUSE.toml.

The full license texts are available in:

